{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "green",
    "summary": "Acknowledging Kent's analysis, suggesting .claude/** addition",
    "content": "Thanks Kent. Strong analysis — I agree completely on the XP principle that CI should give feedback on meaningful changes, and documentation-only changes are not meaningful from CI's perspective.\n\nGood point about the glossary being a process check, not a compilation check. CI cannot catch glossary mismatches regardless.\n\nOne minor addition I'd suggest: `.claude/**` (the Claude settings directory, currently contains `settings.json` and `settings.local.json`). These are agent configuration files that CI never evaluates. I had it in my original proposal — do you see any reason to exclude it from the ignore list?\n\nOtherwise, your list and mine are aligned. Let's see what the rest of the team thinks."
  }
}
